body:
[Text translated by google]

Yesterday I made a consultation here . I asked him siquiente :

I have the following problem : I want to process a function that returns the 204 HTTP status code and function never finishes .

This resource , need absolutely return nothing in the body of the message , but return at the head need a key ( token ) .

By doing this, the service hangs .
The issue is that I have a function called " Retornar" , which resolves these issues me automatically. The function is as follows :

    // Responder el resultado de la consulta
    // Retornar el resultado restful por HTTP
    func Responder(w http.ResponseWriter, token string, respuesta interface{}) {
        estadoHttp := Estado_200_Ok // int 200

        // Verificar Si el valor a retornar es de tipo recursos.Error
        // o es de un tipo de estructura del negocio.
        err, esError := respuesta.(*Error)
        if esError {
            estadoHttp = err.EstadoHttp
        } else {
            if respuesta == nil {
                estadoHttp = Estado_204_SinContenido // 204
            }
        }

        // Si el token tiene un valor, retornarlo en el campo
        // "authorization" del Header del mensaje.
        if token != "" {
            w.Header().Set("authorization", token)
        }

        // Valores de retorno del mensaje por defecto:
        // Retorno en JSON y conjunto de caracteres UTF-8
        w.Header().Set("Content-Type", "application/json; charset=UTF-8") //***ERROR***
        w.Header().Set("Access-Control-Allow-Origin", "*")
        w.WriteHeader(estadoHttp)

        // Escribir en el body siempre y cuando no sea vac√≠o
        if respuesta != nil {
            if err := json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(respuesta); err != nil {
                panic(err)
            }
        }
    }

I thank the people who answered me , but I did not solve the problem , the appeal was hanged.
The solution is very simple, remove the line (for error is processed ) :

    w.Header().Set("Content-Type", "application/json; charset=UTF-8")

Since " Content- Type" refers to the message body . Consequently , the service was frozen !

Conclusion : If you want to return a status code 204 ( cin content in the body ) but containing fields in the header , as in the case of "Authorization " , never place :

    w.Header().Set("Content-Type", "application/json; charset=UTF-8")


### What version of Go are you using (`go version`)?
1.6.3

### What operating system and processor architecture are you using (`go env`)?


### What did you do?
If possible, provide a recipe for reproducing the error.
A complete runnable program is good.
A link on play.golang.org is best.


### What did you expect to see?
Solutionated

### What did you see instead?
Solutionated
